STAT 380 Final Project Feature Engineering and Model Building

Tyler Applegate

Feature Engineering.

Load in libraries.

library(data.table)

Read in data.

test<-fread("./project/volume/data/raw/test_file.csv")
train<-fread("./project/volume/data/raw/training_data.csv")
test_emb<-fread("./project/volume/data/raw/test_emb.csv")
train_emb<-fread("./project/volume/data/raw/training_emb.csv")

Reorganize data using melt function.

train$order<-1:nrow(train)
m_DT<-melt(train,id=c("id","order","text"),variable.name = "reddit")
m_DT<-m_DT[value==1][order(order)][,.(id,reddit)]
m_DT$redditInt<-(as.integer(m_DT$reddit)-1)
m_DT$train<-1

Add reddit / train columns to test.

test$reddit<-NA
test<-test[, c("id","reddit")]
test$redditInt<-NA
test$train<-0

Combine train / test and train_emb / test_emb using rbind.

bind1<-rbind(m_DT, test)
bind2<-rbind(train_emb,test_emb)

Combine both previous binds using cbind to create master table.

master<-cbind(bind1,bind2)

Write to interim data folder.

fwrite(master,"./project/volume/data/interim/master_data.csv")
master[1:10]

Model Building.

Load in libraries.

library(data.table)
library(Rtsne)
library(ggplot2)
library(caret)
library(ClusterR)
library(Metrics)
library(xgboost)

Read in data.

test<-fread("./project/volume/data/raw/test_file.csv")
train<-fread("./project/volume/data/raw/training_data.csv")

example_sub<-fread('./project/volume/data/raw/example_sub.csv')
master<-fread('./project/volume/data/interim/master_data.csv')

Hide information.

master$id<-NULL
master$reddit<-NULL
master$redditInt<-NULL
master$train<-NULL

Perform PCA.

pca<-prcomp(master)

Look at the percent variance explained by each PCA.

screeplot(pca)

Perform xgboost.

Split into train and test.

y.train<-train$redditInt
y.test<-test$redditInt

Work with dummies.

dummies <- dummyVars(redditInt~ ., data = train)
